<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/104912196-hailee-deluca"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1595285235i/104912196._UX100_CR0,38,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/104912196-hailee-deluca">Hailee DeLuca</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Really depends on the reader. This reading was required for my high school English class and there were uncomfortable scenes and even the characters&apos; <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Really depends on the reader. This reading was required for my high school English class and there were uncomfortable scenes and even the characters' ways of speaking sparked discomfort.<br /><br />I wouldn't recommend this collection for anyone under twelve but if you can't handle the material, you'll know within the first few pages.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
