<div id="review_259370208" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/259370208" />
    <a title="mark monday" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/131922-mark-monday"><img alt="mark monday" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1572672245p2/131922.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/259370208?book_show_action=true">Jan 09, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="mark monday" class="user" itemprop="url" name="mark monday" href="/user/show/131922-mark-monday">mark monday</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/131922-mark-monday?shelf=time-to-come-of-age">time-to-come-of-age</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/131922-mark-monday?shelf=mnemonic-devices">mnemonic-devices</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/131922-mark-monday?shelf=these-fragile-lives">these-fragile-lives</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer259370208" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13918232661983298797"><i>read during my Punk Rock Flophouse Years</i><br/><br/><i>I Remember</i>: linked stories about growing up in the Dominican Republic and then New Jersey... a writing style that is rather tight, clean, stripped-down, deadpan... i would have preferred a looser, rowdier writing style... a narrative that is alive and fresh, with scenes that should jump off the page, and sometimes do... feels real... some surprising charm, many laugh-out-loud moments... and yet it feels somehow minor note - i guess that&apos;s life... oh no, am</span>
  <span id="freeText13918232661983298797" style="display:none"><i>read during my Punk Rock Flophouse Years</i><br /><br /><i>I Remember</i>: linked stories about growing up in the Dominican Republic and then New Jersey... a writing style that is rather tight, clean, stripped-down, deadpan... i would have preferred a looser, rowdier writing style... a narrative that is alive and fresh, with scenes that should jump off the page, and sometimes do... feels real... some surprising charm, many laugh-out-loud moments... and yet it feels somehow minor note - i guess that's life... oh no, am i getting a little bored now?... ah well, it is still a worthy effort. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13918232661983298797" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


