    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1264006306" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1264006306" />
    <a title="Tim" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/37256808-tim"><img alt="Tim" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1444088588p2/37256808.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1264006306?book_show_action=true">Apr 25, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tim" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tim" href="/user/show/37256808-tim">Tim</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37256808-tim?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37256808-tim?shelf=new-york">new-york</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1264006306" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12781499443485260448">Here is another literary star that has gotten a lot of attention in recent years. Diaz is a Dominican-American, raised in Washington Heights, NYC. This story cycle centers on one Dominican family that is split between Upper Manhattan and Santo Domingo. Each story shows a different facet of the life of this family, with the focus primarily on the young man known as Junior (or “Yunior”). This is really good, enjoyable writing, even if some of it does seem to have the stamp of an MFA writing studen</span>
  <span id="freeText12781499443485260448" style="display:none">Here is another literary star that has gotten a lot of attention in recent years. Diaz is a Dominican-American, raised in Washington Heights, NYC. This story cycle centers on one Dominican family that is split between Upper Manhattan and Santo Domingo. Each story shows a different facet of the life of this family, with the focus primarily on the young man known as Junior (or “Yunior”). This is really good, enjoyable writing, even if some of it does seem to have the stamp of an MFA writing student’s work. He also uses the no quotation marks style that Irvine Welsh and others have used. Each story is rich in detail, but clean and sharp, and makes its points and moves on, without overstatement. The whole thing has a real feeling to it--not just because of the gritty homeboy/homegirl environment of many of the pieces but because there is believable emotion interwoven through each piece. <br /><br />A couple of the stories feature a teenager called “No Face,” a disfigured kid who had his face bitten by a pig when he was an infant and no wears a cloth face mask. Of course he is treated mercilessly by the other kids. “Aurora” is a nice one, about the love between a young drug dealer and his messed up on and off girlfriend. “Aguantando” is about a young boy waiting to hear from his father, who left the family in DR and went to New York. “Drown” takes a look at homo/bi issues in the hood, and centers on a masculine young man who is avoiding seeing a former best buddy, apparently because of the couple of sexual experiences they had together. “Edison, New Jersey” is the surprisingly entertaining tale of a young guy who delivers pool tables for a living. “How to Date a Browngirl, Blackgirl…” is an amusing look at a young guy’s seduction techniques and experiences. “Negocios” is about the struggle of a newly arrived immigrant in the USA. This is good stuff all the way through.<br /> <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12781499443485260448" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1264006306">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
        <a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link1264006306" title="Flag this review as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=1264006306&amp;resource_type=Review&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F531989.Drown">flag</a>





